"(1) (i) moved quietly through the humming corridors of ’s Central Reactor Complex, his breath fogging in the recycled air as amber emergency lights cast the sterile white walls in a sickly glow. The distant whine of plasma flow and the rhythmic clank of maintenance drones echoed through the metallic passageways, but it was the faint, rising pulse from Bay 7 that drew his attention—a subtle vibration beneath the floorplates, like the first tremor of an approaching storm. Triton Gas Colony. Julian Ross.\n(2) (i) He paused before the reinforced door of the matter synthesizer array, its surface etched with shifting quantum glyphs that now flickered erratically. A shudder ran through the machinery as containment fields buckled, sparks leaping from junctions in a violent cascade. Julian watched, heart hammering, as the core chamber blazed with unstable energy, the air thick with ozone and the unmistakable scent of imminent collapse—the overload was happening right before his eyes. October 27, 2224. witnessed a matter synthesizer overload."